               <p>I am headborough; I took charge of the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178906030080"></xptr>prisoner on Saturday the 30th of May, I produce the prosecutor's shirt; the prisoner said he had left the hat and a shirt at the George, but there was none there; but I found this shirt at the Fitzroy Arms; then the prisoner told me he had sold the hat for eighteen-pence, and his own hat; I received this shirt from 
